{
  "stem": "1338.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my mother was trying to snatch him out, ran around.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But the trucks were already there, and they just shoved them into the trucks like cattle, and I guess that's when he died.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So September 1942 was the critical time for the life of ghetto because we-- all the children disappeared.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now a controversy about the King of Jews or this guy, Chaim Rumkowski, whatever can be said about him, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I, I presume he did help to survive.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "After all, ghetto lasted the longest in the Nazi Germany, and survivors from Lodz are probably the largest percentage of survivors that went through.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I would say that maybe he deserves some credit for it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He claims that that's what he was doing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "On the other hand, he was the one who came out and asked the mothers to give the children, and he was a head of an orphanage before the war.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And you ask yourself the question, you know, what happens to a person like that when you read the memoirs of Adam Czerniakow, who was electrical engineer-- not that I'm biased to him.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In Warsaw, he was the head of the Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when he ask him for the children, he swallowed the cyanide pill.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And after September-- after September '42, things have changed dramatically.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were not children anymore.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were no old ones anymore.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My uncle, the one who never believed that, that people who created Goethe and Beethoven could possibly be that bad, that's the one they picked off the street in September 1942 because he had grey hair.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So by the time that period was over, my father died three months later in December in January 19-- 3rd January 1943.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
